name:                vocabulary
stack:               ( -- )
return stack:        ( -- )
string stack:        ( -- )
contexts:            stateless
input:               ( word )
category:            defining, vocabularies

decription:          read a space delimited string from input, create a vocabulary with
                     the name of that string.

notes:               due to vocabulary name also used as name for the bash array which
                     serves as wordlist, naming is currently restricted to characters
                     which are acceptable for bash variable names. Use of characters
                     a..z, A..Z, 0..9 and _ is safe.

standard:            yes
deviation:           mentioned naming restriction applies currently
